            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Without any experience in facing life,I would have called them the worst school.its TRUE they dont know how to help specially abled ,differently abled but they care and you will feel it only when you need it most.\n\nI won gold medals 1st,2nd and 5th standard in angloindian board boys school,after that I was in a very planned manner exposed to the outside world,today I may be weak and unemployed but only I know how I survived covid.the school only trains you in facing politics with discipline which is very important. Sorry sir for being brutally honest.\n\ni faced lot of partiality and bias in that school.i was not allowed into ncc without any proper reason.the teachers kept demanding rs.5/rs.10 donations every now and then.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
